sorry, but without looking to our logs etc, I bet it's a mod that is not for your version. 

Please make sure every mod you have is for 1.2.2 and not for 1.3 or 1.1.3

You are using 1.3 mods in 1.2.2 which will 100% cause crashes. Below are the ones I've identified as using the 1.3 version (there could be more). You need to start a clean install and only install 1.2.2 versions of mods.

  • Retractable Lifting Surface
  • SXT Continued
  • Modular Flight Integrator
  • KSP Addon Version Checker
  • B9 Procedural Wings
  • Kerbal Alarm Clock
  • RealChute
  • Kerbal Engineering Redux
  • StageRecovery
  • Procedural Parts
  • DMagic Orbital Science
  • TAC Life Support
  • Community Resource Pack
  • Kerbal Attachment System
  • Connected Living Space
  • Universal Storage
  • KRASH
  • Contract Configurer
Edited June 19, 2017 by TheRagingIrishman
interesting i installed mods with ckan:S

6 hours ago, onurycl said:

interesting i installed mods with ckan:S

 

If the netkan hasn't been updated for a parts mod that includes a plugin and that mod is updated to 1.3, CKAN thinks that updated is for 1.2.2 and will install it anyway. This will break your game. You need to remind the author to have the netkan updated to only install for ksp 1.3 so old versions aren't updated with broken plugins.

tx for help guys but i found the problem

i updated all my drivers and problem gone sry for bothering you

it is working now
